<p>A good bookkeeper costs $500-800/month. The mistakes they prevent are worth 5-10x that amount.</p>

<h2 id="heading-29">The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>Bookkeeping mistakes aren't just "accounting errors." They're profit leaks that compound over time.</p>

<p>The businesses that thrive are the ones that treat bookkeeping as a core business function, not an afterthought.</p>

<p>Stop losing money to preventable mistakes. Get your books audited, fix the errors, and put systems in place to prevent them from happening again.</p>

<p>Your bank account will thank you.</p>